The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 23 May is 42,114 (4,874.4 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 18 May, there were 60 new confirmed cases (6.9 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 11 May, there were 103 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 42% (43 fewer cases).
